= Weekly Meal Prep Components

This system creates:

- 7 lunches
- 7 dinners
- interchangeable meal components
- ~1500 calories/day before snacks

---

= Component 1 — Challah Loaf

*Makes 14 servings*

== Ingredients

- 180g warm water
- 50g sugar
- 7g instant yeast
- 500g bread flour
- 80g vegetable oil
- 2 eggs
- 1 egg yolk
- 6g salt

_Optional:_ sesame seeds

== Method

+ Combine water, sugar, yeast.
+ Rest 5 min.
+ Add flour, oil, eggs, yolk, salt.
+ Knead 8–10 min.
+ Rise 90 min.
+ Braid loaf.
+ Rise 45 min.
+ Brush with egg white.
+ Bake at 175C for 25 min.

== Portioning

Slice into 14 portions of 90g. Freeze slices individually.

---

= Component 2 — Roasted Vegetable Mix

*Makes 10 portions*

== Ingredients

- 1200g mushrooms
- 800g onion
- 800g bell pepper
- 40g olive oil
- 10g salt

== Method

+ Slice vegetables.
+ Toss with oil + salt.
+ Roast at 220C for 30–35 min.
+ Stir halfway through.
+ Cool completely.

== Portioning

Portion into 10 containers of 280g. Freeze.

---

= Component 3 — Spinach Base

*Makes 10 portions*

== Ingredients

- 2000g frozen spinach
- 25g garlic
- 15g olive oil
- 8g salt

== Method

1. Heat oil.
2. Cook garlic 1 min.
3. Add spinach.
4. Cook until excess moisture evaporates.

== Portioning

Portion into 10 containers of 180g. Freeze.

---

= Component 4 — Tomato Lentil Base

*Makes 8 portions*

== Ingredients

- 350g dry lentils
- 1000g canned tomatoes
- 300g onion
- 20g garlic
- 15g olive oil
- 8g salt

== Method

+ Cook lentils until tender.
+ Sauté onion in oil.
+ Add garlic.
+ Add tomatoes.
+ Simmer 15 min.
+ Stir in lentils.

== Portioning

Portion into 8 containers of 250g. Freeze.

---

= Component 5 — Cooked Chickpeas

*Makes 8 portions*

== Ingredients

- 500g dry chickpeas
- water
- salt

== Method

+ Soak overnight.
+ Simmer 60–90 min until tender.
+ Cool completely.

== Portioning

Portion into 8 containers of 160g cooked chickpeas. Freeze.

---

= Component 6 — Cooked Pinto Beans

*Makes 8 portions*

== Ingredients

- 500g dry pinto beans
- water
- salt

== Method

+ Soak overnight.
+ Simmer 60–90 min until tender.
+ Cool completely.

== Portioning

Portion into 8 containers of 160g cooked beans. Freeze.

